From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@example.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 15:20:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] pdk: support LoongArch64 in nginx FFI arch check

Kong's PDK nginx module selects the C type used for Nginx connection/request
statistics based on LuaJIT FFI's architecture string.

LoongArch64 LuaJIT reports:

  ffi.arch == "loongarch64"

The existing code only treats `x64` and `arm64` as 64-bit architectures, so
Kong logs `Unsupported arch: loongarch64` during nginx init.

LoongArch64 uses a 64-bit ABI in this build, so use the same uint64_t counter
definitions as x64 and arm64.
---
 kong/pdk/nginx.lua | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kong/pdk/nginx.lua b/kong/pdk/nginx.lua
index 5517742..616cbb7 100644
--- a/kong/pdk/nginx.lua
+++ b/kong/pdk/nginx.lua
@@ -12,7 +12,7 @@ local arch = ffi.arch
 local ngx  = ngx
 local tonumber = tonumber
 
-if arch == "x64" or arch == "arm64" then
+if arch == "x64" or arch == "arm64" or arch == "loongarch64" then
   ffi.cdef[[
     uint64_t *ngx_stat_active;
     uint64_t *ngx_stat_reading;
-- 
